race.description: The Big Screen Company Maiden Plate
race.comment: KOKO (8) won a jumpout and then was narrowly beaten at Kyneton on debut on a heavy track. There was plenty of merit in that effort, and she'll jump fitter and from a low barrier. Stackhouse rides today and she's a strong winning chance. PATH TO PROFIT (9) will be fancied building on her placing here heavily bet. She just missed in town prior and Melham has been booked by the premier stable. Has an inside barrier and may control the race. THEATRICAL QUEEN (12) had been well educated and went well here on debut. Has an awkward gate to overcome, but with the extra fitness she can get some of the money. FAERIE (3) also needs to find more to be winning, but she's sure to keep improving for a leading metro stable.
